  <h1>Privacy Policy for Tiny Math</h1>
  <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> October&nbsp;2025</p>

  <h2>1. Overview</h2>
  <p><em>Tiny Math</em> is an educational app developed by Pietro Nicholls. We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting it.</p>

  <h2>2. No Data Collection</h2>
  <p>Tiny Math does <strong>not collect, store, share, or transmit any personal information</strong>. The app runs entirely on your device and does not connect to any external servers or analytics services.</p>

  <h2>3. Children’s Privacy</h2>
  <p>Tiny Math is suitable for young learners and complies with COPPA and GDPR-K requirements. Because no data is collected, no information about children is ever stored or transmitted.</p>

  <h2>4. Advertising and Tracking</h2>
  <p>The app contains <strong>no advertising, tracking, or third-party analytics</strong>.</p>

  <h2>5. In-App Purchases (Future Versions)</h2>
  <p>Future updates may include optional paid features or subscriptions processed securely by Apple Inc. through the App Store. No payment or personal data is handled by the developer.</p>

  <h2>6. Security</h2>
  <p>Because Tiny Math does not transmit data, there is no remote storage or risk of interception. All interactions remain local to your device.</p>

  <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>This policy may be updated to reflect new features or legal requirements. The latest version will always be available at this page.</p>

  <h2>8. Contact</h2>
  <p>For any questions about this policy, please contact:<br>
     <strong>Pietro Nicholls</strong><br>
     Email: <a href="mailto:pietro_n@hotmail.co.uk">pietro_n@hotmail.co.uk</a></p>

  <p><em>© 2025 Pietro Nicholls. All rights reserved.</em></p>
